(B[m[?1l>[H[2J[?12l[?25h[?1000l[?1002l[?1006l[?1005l]112[?25l[1;1HWelcome to our EEL5718 Project Demo[K
[K
Team:[K
Khaled Hassan[K
Samuel Lichtenheld[K
[K
Project:[K
End to End Message Transmission with Encryption and Authentication using Socket Programming[K
[K
Features:[K
Client transmits files (text or binary) or anything sent to the client's stdin (until EOF) to the server.[K
The server saves the files and prints the messages recieved to the server's stdout.[K
[K
The message is encrypted using AES256-CBC, and then HMAC-SHA256 is applied to both the[K
encrypted payload and the encryption IV.[K
[K
The encrypted payload, the IV, and the HMAC signature are all converted to base64 strings[K
and concatenated together, separated by "." (inspired by JSON Web Tokens https://jwt.io).[K
[K
The server verifies the signature on the transmitted information before attempting to decrypt the payload.[21;1HIf an attacker modifies the encrypted payload or the IV, the si

gnature will not match. If the signature[K
is modified, it also will not match. This provides integrity over the entire message.[K
[K
It is especially important to authenticate the payload because the encrypted message is actually a[K
serialized data structure (using the built-in Python pickle library). This library says that it[K
is important not to deserialize an object from an untrusted source. Because the message is successfully[K
authenticated, we consider it trusted (and not maliciously constructed).[K
[K
